Oh also
Asking to export the list as XML natively does take a time.... As the progress are being made on their server. So sending request to export the list everyday can affect your account to be questioned as well, or you'll have burden to download the exported list manually everyday.

Heya! Thanks for reminding me to put aniDB to planned services that I accidentally forgot to list it (lol)
However, although yes I could able to possibly integrate aniDB mylist as I learned a lot of stuff on Python for a year now, I have some concern regarding aniDB itself.
aniDB developer experience is really archaic at best. Their API access mainly uses UDP protocol which I'd say, none of the services used it but aniDB, and even sending the command to its API must be really careful. If the command were sent simultaneously without delay, oh boy, your account or even your IP address can get banned. Additionally, I personally don't know how to handle UDP commands, so using it might require me to sacrifice my IP instead.
Although they have read-only HTTP API, it only applicable for Anime information instead, not all-purpose.
Scraping HTML of mylist can risk of your account/ip to get banned, so I definitely want to avoid this, as the aniDB maintainers themselves explicitly didn't allow html scrapping. bokusu will be intended as Async-based package module/cli app since I want to make this module to be supported to my another Anime program project, miirakuru. Most of the libraries available in pypi are sync-based, which could break bokusu .
Those all are my concerns about aniDB to be integrated to the module. I can make an opt-in system to allow scraping html of mylist, however no support will be given if anything happened to the account/IP.

div.div: Akuyaku Reijou Level 99: Watashi wa Ura Boss desu ga Maou de wa Arimasen

This college kid wants nothing more than a quiet life. So when shes reborn as Yumiella, the hidden villainess of an Otome RPG, shes not exactly thrilled. Still yearning for peace, she abandons her evil duties to live a more discreet life. Until her gamer side kicks in and she accidentally reaches level 99! Now, everyone suspects that shes the infamous Demon Lord. What future awaits her?
(Source: Crunchyroll)

Making up for her sins in a past life as the evil princess Elise, Aoi Takamoto dedicates her life to saving people as a doctor. But a fatal accident cuts her atonement short and suddenly shes back to her previous life, 10 years before her death! Will her foresight and medical brilliance help her change her past ways and heal an ailing empire, or is fate doomed to repeat itself?
(Source: Crunchyroll)

As the war between the Imperial Army and Hellhorde rages on, the Princess, despite being armed with her mythical sword Excalibur, is captured and imprisoned. What kind of torture does she face at the hands of the chief demon interrogator? Fluffy fresh-baked toast! Hot, steaming ramen! Oh, the humanity! Can the Princess withstand these tormenting treats and keep her kingdoms secrets safe? (Source: Crunchyroll)

All Fuuko wants is a passionate romance like the one in her favorite shoujo manga. Unfortunately, her Unluck ability makes that impossible. But just as Fuuko hits rock bottom, Andy sweeps her off her feetliterally! Now she's become Andy's unwilling test subject as he works to find a way to trigger a stroke of Unluck big enough to kill him for good. However, when the pair discovers a secret organization is hunting them, it puts Andy's burial plans on hold.
(Source: Viz Media)
